Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper investigates the area spectral efficiency (ASE) of a two-tier network with multi-antenna base stations (BSs), which is a key metric in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of a two-tier cellular network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Computer Communications and Networks): The paper deals with the communication aspect of a two-tier cellular network and how the deployment of small-cell BSs can improve the ASE. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper may be relevant to multiagent systems as it considers the interaction between multiple base stations and users in a cellular network. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper may be relevant to systems and control as it analyzes the performance of a complex system (two-tier cellular network) and derives optimal conditions for maximizing ASE.
